1.6.0
  Precompression + bundling correctness (slicejs-cli 4.0.x):
  - `slice build --compress` writes .gz + max-quality .br next to every text
    asset in dist/; `slice start` serves the precompressed variant per the
    client's Accept-Encoding (brotli preferred). Opt-in (brotli max is slow).
    Node zlib only, no new deps. A 900 KB bundle → ~100 KB brotli on the wire.
  - Bundle grouping fix: the budget rebalancer used to split a shared bundle
    (shared-core) into parts by an INFLATED size (it counted every file in a
    component folder, incl. non-code assets) and left the referrers pointing at
    a bundle key that no longer existed → dead orphan bundles + a dangling ref
    on every route using shared code. Now shared-core is pinned (never split),
    budgeting uses code size (js/html/css only), and a referential-integrity
    check warns on any dangling/orphan bundle. Runtime unchanged.
  - Runtime load model (for reference): only the `critical` bundle blocks first
    paint; a route's other bundles are idle-preloaded (requestIdleCallback) and
    cached, with an individual-component fallback. So transfer size (→ compress)
    matters more than splitting a shared bundle finer.
