1.3.0
  External dependencies + public/ folder + build validation (slicejs-cli 3.8.x):
  - npm packages via BARE IMPORTS now work (`import dayjs from 'dayjs'`),
    resolved from node_modules with esbuild — same resolver in dev and build,
    no config. CJS/ESM/UMD, exports maps, scoped, subpaths, transitive deps,
    dynamic import('pkg'); package CSS injected, WASM/images/fonts inlined.
    Dev rewrites bare specifiers to /@slice-modules/<pkg> (cached in
    node_modules/.slice-deps); build bundles once (shared -> vendor-shared).
    Replaces the old "vendor into src/libs + publicFolders" pattern.
  - publicFolders REMOVED. Static assets live under src/public/ (served at the
    root URL, copied into the build) — Themes/Styles/images moved there; no
    config key. Absolute imports kept only when the file exists under public/.
  - Build-time prop validation: `slice build` runs the doctor prop checks and
    BLOCKS on definition errors (unknown type, schema/items/allowedValues
    mismatch); style issues warn. Bypass with --no-validate.
  - New flags: `slice build --strict-external` (fail on unresolved npm deps),
    `--no-validate`. slice doctor also checks props + npm imports missing from
    node_modules.
  - Gotcha added: `context.enabled` requires `events.enabled` — build hard-fails
    otherwise (ContextManager reactivity runs through EventManager).
