1.2.0
  Event Registry + pub/sub tracing (slicejs-web-framework 3.4.4):
  - slice.events.register(catalog) / register(namespace, catalog): opt-in,
    mergeable catalog of events. Declares 'domain:action' keys + payload
    mini-schema. Dev validation is warn-only (undeclared + no-namespace),
    never throws, silent in production. Loose mode unchanged when never called.
  - Typed events: `slice types generate` reads the catalog -> SliceEventRegistry,
    typing emit/subscribe (wrong payload fails tsc). Catalog arg must be an
    object literal / imported literal (same rule as static props).
  - Pub/sub tracing in two layers: STATIC (generate writes
    src/slice-events.generated.js mapping each event to emitter/listener call
    sites — documentation, no execution) + RUNTIME (emit attributed to its
    component via bind, or a stack-trace file:line; recorded only while the
    Events panel is open). Debugger Registry tab = static graph; Subscribers/
    History = live. slice.events.loadGraph / staticEmittersOf / staticListenersOf.
  - Leak Inspector (dev-only, config `debugger.leakInspector`, `alt+shift+k`):
    surfaces components registered but detached from the DOM (the
    innerHTML=''-without-destroyComponent leak), with retain chain, a per-row
    destroy probe, and a growing-trend signal. Excludes cached Route/MultiRoute
    (`__sliceCached`); extensible via slice.controller.registerLeakExclusion(fn);
    programmatic slice.controller.findOrphans().
