1.1.0
  In-place reactive refresh best practices (slicejs-web-framework 3.4.4):
  - update() documented as the UNIVERSAL in-place refresh hook, called by the
    Router / a parent / the component itself / a context.watch callback — and
    OPTIONAL (most components refresh through their setters). The framework
    WRAPS update(): serialize + coalesce re-entrance + liveness (skips the
    commit if destroyed mid-refresh), so it is written plainly, no guards.
  - setComponentProps now auto-detects build vs refresh. Refresh applies only
    the passed props (no defaults, no required check, diff-guards honored,
    omitted props kept). Added facade slice.setComponentProps + slice.isComponentAlive.
  - Refresh-in-place guidance: setter (default) -> setComponentProps (many
    props) -> update() (async/custom). Lists: reuse by stable sliceId
    (build new / update existing / destroy gone). Total replacement:
    build-then-swap. Never invent a render() method.
  - Stronger leak rule: never innerHTML='' / replaceChildren / remove over
    slice.build'd children without destroyComponent/destroyByContainer first;
    release window/document listeners, timers, and observers in beforeDestroy().
